Need:
8GB or up USB drive
MS ISO file
A macOS system

Start:
1.Open terminal
2.Enter: diskutil list
3.Find your disk name like disk2 (/dev/disk2(external, physical))
4.Enter: diskutil eraseDisk ExFat "WINDOWS10" MBR disk# (change # to your USB drive # like disk2)
5.Double click open Windows10.ISO
6.Enter: cp -rp /Volumes/CCCOMA_X64FRE_EN-US_DV9/* /Volumes/WINDOWS10/ (Change the file ISO name your downloaded, mine is CCCOMA_X64FRE_EN-US_DV9)
7.Wait and terminal will shows a row start with "~"
8.Finish
